President Donald J. Trump spoke with Prime Minister Theresa May of the United Kingdom about the terrorist attack in Manchester, England. They both condemned the attack, which targeted teenagers and their friends. President Trump reassured Prime Minister May that the United States stands with the UK and offered American aid in the investigation. They praised the response to the attack and discussed their commitment to defeating terrorism. President Trump also mentioned his upcoming meeting with Prime Minister May to discuss their countries' commitment to each other and their efforts in fighting terrorism.